                p Chen is a ceramic artist who lives and works in Taipei. Chen’s creative practice is inspired by everyday life, such as markets, food, plants, etc. Through deconstructing and transforming these with his personal touch, Chen tries to represent people’s common life experiences, in oder to resonate with his audience. Although he mainly works with clay, Chen also juxtaposes and combines ceramic works with other materials and ready-made objects. These massive and rapidly manufactured daily objects reflect a contemporary life. In contrast, the pottery and other objects fire off each other, and that is what Chen aims for: capturing a possible harmony between these conflicts.
